Installing docker : 

~ distro binaries packages through apt , yum >> but version could be old

~ https://get.docker.com
> copy past to shell the following command:
>> # curl -fsSL get.docker.com -o get-docker.sh <<
>>> it checks the distro and intall docker last flavour

# docker info

# ls -lh /var/run/docker.sock 
>> to check group and permission
>> add user to docker group : ex 
# usermod -aG docker user 
or 
# gpasswd -a student docker

~ /etc/default/docker is the file where we can chnage the way to administrate docker : remotely, localy or use an HTTP proxy

~ everything is on /var/lib/docker
